Legislators elected under the banner of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) in the North East geopolitical zone have passed a vote of confidence on the leadership of the Mai Mala Buni-led national caretaker committee of the party. The vote of confidence was passed during an extraordinary meeting of the Conference of Nigeria States Legislators, North East zone held at Hazibal Hotel, Bauchi on Thursday led by the Speaker of Bauchi State House of Assembly, Abubakar Y. Suleiman. The lawmakers observed that the Buni committee has done well by trying to make the APC a united entity as can be seen in the number of state governors, legislators and other personalities who have decamped to the party. The meeting also agreed to speak with one voice in the choice of presidential candidate of the party stressing that it is only by doing so that the zone can have a definite say in the political affairs of the country.